thread.title: New Jersey’s Maria Argenzia of RE/MAX Property Center Wins Award
thread.title_full: New Jersey’s Maria Argenzia of RE/MAX Property Center Wins 2015 Five Star Real Estate Agent Award

author: Five Star Professional Representative
title: New Jersey’s Maria Argenzia of RE/MAX Property Center Wins Award
text:
“To achieve this honor is a testament to the consistent hard work and commitment I offer to my clients. Servicing my clients with integrity, communication, negotiation and satisfaction are important to me. Thank you to my clients for taking the time to recommend me. It is both rewarding and satisfying to know I am making a positive impact,” says Maria. Maria Argenzia, RE/MAX Property Center , is featured March issue of New Jersey Monthly as a 2015 Five winner.
 New Jersey Monthly to identify and showcase an exclusive group of real estate agents who have demonstrated excellence in their field. Less than 7 percent of agents in the New Jersey area received this recognition.
The 2015 Five winners have been carefully selected for their commitment to professional excellence and overall client satisfaction. The award is based on rigorous research providing quality services.
“In October, I will be celebrating 30 years as a licensed Realtor and 28 of those years with RE/MAX. I have received many awards along the way! RE/MAX Hall of Fame, Life Member NJAR® Distinguished Sales Club® and the Five for 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2015. I do what I do because I love it,” says Maria Argenzia.
“Five Star Professional’s research is extensive, with more than 10 million consumers, peers and other stakeholders contacted each year. We are relentless in our efforts to identify those professionals with the utmost standard of excellence,” says Jonathan Wesser, Senior Research Manager, Five Star Professional.
Maria Argenzia’s Five Star award profile can be viewed here .
